                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.6363 African Exploration and Development
                    Corp./22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-05T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 5, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 5—6:52
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>424. I conveyed the information contained in the Department’s 240, September 3, 4
                    p.m. and 241, September 3, 6 p.m., to the Acting Under Secretary yesterday
                    morning who was grateful for the confirmation of the reports the Foreign Office
                    had received. He further expressed appreciation for your prompt and sufficient
                    action which he intimated had made their path much easier.</p>
                <pb facs="0886" n="784" xml:id="pg_784"/>
                <p>Subsequently he wrote me a note which I received this morning asking that Sir
                    Samuel Hoare’s thanks be added to his. Foreign Secretary is for the moment
                    confined to his house.</p>
                <p>I venture to point out that at no time in my discussions at the Foreign Office
                    has any reference been made to the so-called American oil concession.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
